<HEAD>Bolan, Iowa, Residents Off to Letterman Show</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By GREG SMITH</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>BOLAN, Iowa (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Volleyball and bowling leagues, two big attractions this time of year in northern <LOCATION> Iowa </LOCATION>, will play second fiddle tonight to <ORGANIZATION> NBC-TV </ORGANIZATION>'s `` Late Night With <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Letterman </PERSON>.'' <PERSON> Letterman </PERSON>'s show will feature the town of <LOCATION> Bolan </LOCATION> _ all 16 residents. `` I do n't think there's anybody in <LOCATION> Worth </LOCATION> <LOCATION> County </LOCATION> that wo n't be watching it,'' said <PERSON> Diane </PERSON> <PERSON> VanHorn </PERSON>, a secretary in the county sheriff's department. At JJ's tavern in <LOCATION> Northwood </LOCATION>, home of about 2,000 people, <PERSON> Larry </PERSON> and <PERSON> Judy </PERSON> <PERSON> Jorgensen </PERSON> are planning a `` Bolan Bonus'' night, featuring a `` Bolan cocktail'' and a `` Bolan burrito.'' `` We were going to promote Wednesday night as ` <ORGANIZATION> Northwood </ORGANIZATION> _ the suburb of <PERSON> Bolan </PERSON>,'' <PERSON> Jorgensen </PERSON> said. Mrs. <PERSON> Jorgensen </PERSON> said the usual crowd that comes to her place after volleyball and bowling leagues will likely stay a little longer to watch `` Late Night'' on the color TV above the bar. `` If I had any influence with those people in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>, I'd have them put the <LOCATION> Bolan </LOCATION> people on at the very end of the show so everybody will stay longer,'' she said. Area residents are proud of the Bolanites, who will be seated together in the `` Late Night'' audience before being introduced. One or two will be on stage with <PERSON> Letterman </PERSON>. The show and all the national attention has given the little town a big-city attitude. <PERSON> Bolan </PERSON> residents have arranged for friends to stay at each of their homes, and they've hired additional security officers to protect their belongings while they are being wined and dined in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION>. Sheriff <PERSON> Chuck </PERSON> <PERSON> Storffregen </PERSON>'s deputies also will patrol the town at all hours until the homeowners return.
