<FIRST>r a PM-SpeechDemons-Example     03-01 0274</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Speech Demons-Example,0276</SECOND>
<HEAD>This Be Talkin' Terrible? Yup, You Betcha</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-Speech Demons</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 An example of the `` speech demons'' targeted for extinction in the <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION> schools: `` <PERSON> Fred </PERSON> says he was n't doin' nuttin'. So, I says to him, ` I'm goin' to da liberry, I'll meetcha there. But he did n't know where da liberry was at. I axe him, ` Are youse foolin' round? It's like, in midtown, you know. Pacifically, at da cau-nuh of 41st and Fifth.' He axes me if I was on' y goin' to da liberry. No, I says. ` What-cha doin' next?' he axed. ` First,' I says, ` I'm goin' to da museum to see some pitchers. Then, I'm goin' to see <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON> _ he be sick, and he ai n't got no food. I brang some soup for him.' I says I think this is da right thing to do. ` Yup, you betcha,' <PERSON> Fred </PERSON> says.'' Now, the same encounter rendered in proper English. `` <PERSON> Fred </PERSON> said he was n't doing anything. I told him, ` I'm going to the library. I'll meet you there.' He did n't know where the library was. I asked him, ` Are you fooling around? It's in midtown. Specifically, it's at the corner of 41st Street and Fifth Avenue.' He asked me if I was going only to the library. No, I said. ` What are you doing next?' he asked. ` First,' I said, I'm going to the museum to see some pictures. Then, I'm going to see <PERSON> Lorenzo </PERSON> _ he's sick and he has no food I brought some soup for him.' I said I thought this was the right thing to do. ` Yes, you're right,' <PERSON> Fred </PERSON> said.
