<HEAD>Cunningham Dance Company Opens</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: No PMs Planned</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By MARY CAMPBELL</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> Merce </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Cunningham </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Dance </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Company </ORGANIZATION> opened its season at the City Center on Tuesday with the premiere of `` Five Stone Wind,'' and the choreographer himself was among the dancers. For much of this 55-minute work, the stage is full of dancers but all are motionless except one or two. The primary motif consists of standing on one foot while stretching, bending and rotating the other leg. This is not a dance that flows. There are many entrances and exits, from five different points. Only occasionally do dancers move in unison or as duet partners. <PERSON> Cunningham </PERSON>, who will turn 70 in April, does arm stretches, bends and turns, usually in the back of the group, once on stage alone. One would expect him to look silly among his trim, young dancers. But he fits the tone of the dance and makes one think about the effectiveness of one or two more mature dancers in the bunch. <PERSON> Cunningham </PERSON> is inventive enough, even pursuing one choreographic idea, to keep one interested throughout. Also, we like long dances so the evening is n't spent mainly in intermissions between short dances. Still, we became restless before the end. Costumes are leotard tops and skirts or pants, later leotards only for the women, in varying colors chosen by <PERSON> Mark </PERSON> <PERSON> Lancaster </PERSON>. The score was created by <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Cage </PERSON>, <PERSON> Takehisa </PERSON> <PERSON> Kosugi </PERSON> and <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> Tudor </PERSON> and has a few painfully loud bursts of sound. The first part of `` Five Stone Wind'' had its premier in <LOCATION> Berlin </LOCATION> last June. The complete work bowed at the Festival d'Avignon in <LOCATION> France </LOCATION> in July. The evening began with <PERSON> Cunningham </PERSON>'s 1968 `` RainForest.'' The company's <ORGANIZATION> City </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> season runs through March 12, and two other premieres are scheduled: `` Cargo X'' and `` Field and Figures.'' The company will perform at the <ORGANIZATION> Leicester </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Festival </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> England </LOCATION> March 16 to 18, at the <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Arizona </ORGANIZATION> in Tempe April 1 and 2, <ORGANIZATION> Kennedy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> Washington </LOCATION> May 1 through 7 and C.W. <ORGANIZATION> Post </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> College </ORGANIZATION> on <LOCATION> Long </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Island </LOCATION> May 12. During July and August the company will dance in <LOCATION> Italy </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> France </LOCATION>.
