<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> Prime Minister <PERSON> Yitzhak </PERSON> <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON>, in an interview published today, called the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> dialogue with the <ORGANIZATION> Palestine </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> `` useless'' and said Chairman <PERSON> Yasser </PERSON> <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON> and <PERSON> Adolf </PERSON> <PERSON> Hitler </PERSON> `` belong to the same family of demagogues and totalitarians.'' If <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON> flew to <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> as the late Egyptian President <PERSON> Anwar </PERSON> <PERSON> Sadat </PERSON> did on a 1977 peace mission, `` we'd put him in prison,'' <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON> told <ORGANIZATION> The </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Washington </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Times </ORGANIZATION>. Interviewed in <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION> by <PERSON> Arnaud </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Borchgrave </PERSON>, the Times' editor-in-chief, the <LOCATION> Israeli </LOCATION> leader called King <PERSON> Hussein </PERSON> of <LOCATION> Jordan </LOCATION>, with whom he has offered to negotiate terms for an Arab-Israeli settlement, an `` element of stability'' in the <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> But, <PERSON> Shamir </PERSON> said, if a <LOCATION> Palestinian </LOCATION> state is to be established it should be located on the <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> <LOCATION> of </LOCATION> <LOCATION> the </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Jordan </LOCATION> <LOCATION> River </LOCATION>, where <PERSON> Hussein </PERSON>'s kingdom stands. `` If the <LOCATION> Jordanian </LOCATION> population one day decides to have a <LOCATION> Palestinian </LOCATION> state there, it's up to them,'' he said. Although <PERSON> Jordan </PERSON> does not provide precise population figures it is believed to be at least 70 percent Palestinian. The <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> B