eeches about class struggle. <PERSON> Clavelle </PERSON> says he will maintain the ideals of the city's Progressives He angered some of them when in his first batch of campaign literature, he described himself as an `` independent'' rather than as a Progressive. And he does not embrace the socialist label as <PERSON> Sanders </PERSON> does. But he says he wants to look out for the elderly, the poor and `` the little guy.'' `` I'm no <PERSON> Bernie </PERSON> <PERSON> Sanders </PERSON>,'' <PERSON> Clavelle </PERSON> said. `` Our backgrounds are different, our styles are different, but our political visions are the same.''
