<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A man who picked up parcels the <ORGANIZATION> Customs </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> had singled out as suspicious was charged with smuggling more than $ 500,000 worth of anabolic steroids into the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> from <LOCATION> Brazil </LOCATION>, authorities said. About 135,000 doses of the body-building drug in pill and injection form were seized over the weekend, said <PERSON> Edgar </PERSON> <PERSON> Adamson </PERSON>, customs agent in charge in <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION>. `` At one time, at one location, this is the largest shipment ever confiscated, we believe,'' <PERSON> Adamson </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Lowell </PERSON> <PERSON> D. </PERSON> <PERSON> Coble </PERSON>, 49, was charged in federal court on Tuesday with four counts of smuggling and possessing the drugs for distribution. The charges are punishable by up to eight years in prison and a $ 500,000 fine. <PERSON> Coble </PERSON> was freed on $ 25,000 bond, said <PERSON> Garry </PERSON> <PERSON> Grotewold </PERSON>, supervisory deputy for the <LOCATION> U.S </LOCATION>. Marshal's office. Authorities said a <ORGANIZATION> Customs </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> mail technician at <LOCATION> Los </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Angeles </LOCATION> <LOCATION> International </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Airport </LOCATION> spotted several suspicious looking parcels marked for delivery to a <LOCATION> Southern </LOCATION> <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> post office box. After <PERSON> Coble </PERSON> picked up the parcels and was arrested, authorities found lists indicated he had customers throughout the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION>, according to a customs affidavit. `` Steroid seizures have been increasing rapidly during the past three years, with about a tenfold increase every year,'' said <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> Hensley </PERSON>, assistant regional commissi