<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A growing number of Americans are filing simpler tax forms, apparently because the new tax law reduced or eliminated several beneficial deductions. The number filing the long Form 1040 is down 4.2 percent this year, the <ORGANIZATION> Internal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Revenue </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Service </ORGANIZATION> said Wednesday. The number filing the `` short'' Form 1040A is up 7.5 percent; 6.8 percent more taxpayers are filing the simplest form, 1040EZ, than at this time last year. `` These figures suggest that many taxpayers who filed Form 1040 in the past may be switching to the simpler, shorter forms,'' the <ORGANIZATION> IRS </ORGANIZATION> said. The 1986 tax overhaul eliminated deductions for state and local sales taxes and two-earner couples, and began phasing out the deduction for consumer interest. It also reduced writeoffs for medical expenses, and for millions of workers it cut or eliminated deductions for Individual Retirement Accounts. Through Feb. 24, halfway through the filing season, the <ORGANIZATION> IRS </ORGANIZATION> had received 30.8 million returns _ only about 28 percent of the 109 million expected to file this year. That is up 2 percent from the 30.2 million at this time last year. This year's receipts included 13.1 million Forms 1040, 8.5 million 1040A and 9.1 million 1040EZ. The <ORGANIZATION> IRS </ORGANIZATION> had processed almost half the returns and had approved refund checks for almost 8.3 million taxpayers, up 9in the <LOCATION> Black </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Hills </LOCATION> of <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Dakota </LOCATION>. Partly cloudy skies and mild temperatures prevailed in the <LOCATION> Southwest </LOCATION>. Temperatures around the nation at 2 p.m. EST ranged from 11 below zero at <LOCATION> Warroad </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Minn. </LOCATION>, to 85 degrees at <LOCATION> Avon </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Park </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Fla </LOCATION>. The morning low for the nation was minus 33 at <