ld within 60 days after the merger is complete. The master limited partnership, formed through the company's <ORGANIZATION> Petrolane </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> subsidiary in 1987, serves the international liquid petroleum gas market <ORGANIZATION> Panhandle </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> is financing 80 percent, or $ 2.6 billion, of its $ 3.2 billion takeover along with $ 1.05 billion in refinancing and working capital, <PERSON> Hart </PERSON> said. The $ 1.7 billion in interim financing is included in the figures. <ORGANIZATION> Panhandle </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION>'s $ 53-a-share cash tender offer came weeks after <ORGANIZATION> Texas </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> rejected as inadequate Houston-based <ORGANIZATION> Coastal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>'s $ 2.6 billion takeover bid. <ORGANIZATION> Coastal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> has extended its offer but has not said whether it intends to increase the $ 42-a-share cash bid.
